  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>tortillas</strong> to a baking tray&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle them with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season them with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 10-15 min or until they're golden and crispy - these are your <strong>crispy tortillas</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/my-big-fat-warm-greek-salad/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and cut the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span>&nbsp;</strong>into wedges, then separate the<strong> red onion wedges</strong> into 'petals'</p>\r\n<p>Top, tail and slice the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>tomatoes</strong> into wedges&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/my-big-fat-warm-greek-salad/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> tomato wedges</strong>&nbsp;to a&nbsp;separate baking tray with the <strong>feta</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sprinkle the<strong> tomato wedges</strong> and<strong> feta</strong> with the&nbsp;<strong>dried oregano</strong> and drizzle them both with<strong> olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 8-10 min or until the<strong> tomato wedges</strong>&nbsp;and the<strong> feta</strong>&nbsp;are hot to touch</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/my-big-fat-warm-greek-salad/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>olive oil&nbsp;</strong>over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the&nbsp;<strong>red onion petals&nbsp;</strong>with a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt&nbsp;</strong>and a small splash of<strong>&nbsp;water</strong>, cover with a lid and cook for 3-4 min or until they're beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/my-big-fat-warm-greek-salad/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once done, add the<strong> sliced courgette</strong> to the red&nbsp;onion and cook for 3 min, stirring occasionally or until lightly browned and cooked but retaining a slight bite</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/my-big-fat-warm-greek-salad/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>black</strong>&nbsp;<strong>olives</strong> and<strong> capers</strong> together roughly and add them to a large mixing bowl</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>red wine vinegar</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> - this is your<strong> Greek</strong>&nbsp;<strong>dressing&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Pick the<strong> dill leaves</strong> from their stalks and tear them apart&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/my-big-fat-warm-greek-salad/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Break the <strong>crispy</strong><strong><strong>&nbsp;</strong>tortilla shards </strong>up into rough uneven pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Remove the <strong>warmed feta</strong> and<strong> tomato wedges</strong> from the oven and leave the<strong> feta</strong> to cool for 3-4 min (this stops it falling apart)</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>cooked courgette,</strong>&nbsp;<strong>onion</strong>, <strong>tortilla shards</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;tomato wedges</strong> and<strong> dill leaves&nbsp;</strong> to the <strong>Greek</strong>&nbsp;<strong>dressing</strong> and give everything a good mix - this is your <strong>warm Greek salad</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/my-big-fat-warm-greek-salad/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>baked feta</strong> over the <strong>warm Greek salad&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Garnish with the<strong>&nbsp;sumac</strong></p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
